Statistics
[[Image:Statistics.gif|thumb|Yeah, it's pretty and all, but WHAT DOES IT MEAN?!?!?!?]] 
[[Image:Venn-ed-fx.png|thumb|Statistics can be displayed using a [[venn diagram]]]]
[[Image:Pac man pie chart.jpg|thumb|Pie charts can also be effective debate tools]]

[[Statistics]] are numbers.  These numbers can be used, finessed, and cited in order to [[pwn]] someone in a [[debate]], or to make yourself look more [[Intelligence|intelligent]] than you actually are.  Whether these numbers are actually [[fact|factual]] or properly collected is irrelevant.  

Most people who use statistics in everyday life are [[loser|lusers]] who are too busy crunching numbers to leave their [[basement dwelling]].

The unfortunate corollary is that most people who focus on statistics are [[rich and beautiful]]. 

[[Some argue]] that 43% of all statistics are [[Shit nobody cares about|completely useless]].

==Famous Statistics==

These statistics constitute [[common knowledge]], and should be used in any debate in order to [[pwn]] your foe.  (The best part of using statistics in debate is that ''[[Noone|no one]] can tell if you [[lies|lie]]''.)  Remember:  94% of [[liberals]] hate statistics!

